  "prompt": "Why do most North Indians love rajma chawal?",
  "response": "Rajma Chawal is a beloved dish in North India for several reasons:\n\n1. Cultural significance\n- Traditional Punjabi cuisine staple\n- Comfort food passed down through generations\n- Reminds people of home-cooked meals\n\n2. Taste and flavor\n- Rich, creamy rajma (kidney bean) curry\n- Spicy and aromatic masala\n- Pairs perfectly with steamed rice\n- Balanced and satisfying taste profile\n\n3. Nutritional value\n- High protein content from kidney beans\n- Good source of essential nutrients\n- Wholesome and filling meal\n\n4. Easy to prepare\n- Simple ingredients\n- Can be cooked in large quantities\n- Suitable for everyday meals and social gatherings\n\n5. Affordability\n- Kidney beans are relatively inexpensive\n- Ingredients are easily available\n- Cost-effective nutritious meal\n\n6. Emotional connection\n- Often associated with childhood memories\n- Nostalgic dish for many North Indians\n- Represents home and family cooking\n\n7. Vegetarian-friendly\n- Suits vegetarian dietary preferences\n- Popular in a region with significant vegetarian population\n\nThese factors contribute to Rajma Chawal's popularity and cultural significance in North Indian cuisine.",
